OL,4,C'Quarter of adopted families' in crisis
OL,5, More than a quarter of adopted families
OL,6, are in crisis, according to a survey by
OL,7, the BBC and charity Adoption UK. 
OL,9,FMore than half of those surveyed
OL,10,Freported living with a child who was
OL,11,Fviolent, including being punched,
OL,12,Fkicked or threatened with knives. 
OL,14,FMore serious incidents included
OL,15,Fhospital visits and sexual assault. 
OL,17,FDespite the challenges, most families
OL,18,Fsaid they were glad they adopted.
OL,19,FAdoption UK said families needed
OL,20,Fskilled help and support.
